On July 12, 2013, the White House announced that President Obama signed three bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 324, awards a congressional gold medal to the First Special Service Force for their service during World War II. The second bill, H.R. 1151, directs the Secretary of State to develop a strategy to obtain observer status for Taiwan at the International Civil Aviation Organization Assembly and other related meetings. The third bill, H.R. 2383, designates the new Interstate 70 bridge over the Mississippi River as the "Stan Musial Veterans Memorial Bridge."